<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="410" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1297,1898]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1333,1358]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Cheliceral retromargins unidentate, both promarginal teeth of similar size, small. Each frontal spur small and cone-like, ventral one small and tooth-like (
<figureCitation box="[757,829,1369,1394]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[190,1395,183,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[190,1396,183,1925]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Opisthoncus bellus (Karsch, 1878), male syntype. A: general appearance, dorsal view (with shape of cephalothorax); B: cephalothorax, frontal view (with chelicera); C – D: abdomen, lateral and dorsal views; E – F: chelicerae, ventral and lateral views; G – J: palpal organ, ventral and retrolateral views. Scale bars A, C, D: 1 mm; H, J: 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246502/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
Figs 
<number box="[814,829,1370,1393]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
B, E, F). Fangs with internal outgrowths. Differs from related 
<taxonomicName box="[234,397,1405,1430]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hyllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbipalpis">
<emphasis box="[234,254,1406,1429]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[268,397,1405,1430]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">barbipalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by relatively shorter palpal tibia (about 
<number box="[847,876,1405,1430]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" value="65.0">65</number>
% of cymbium length) and truncate cymbium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="410" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1297,1898]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1441,1466]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[354,411,1441,1466]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Male</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[422,509,1442,1466]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">syntype</typeStatus>
(in bad condition, 
<figureCitation box="[734,805,1441,1466]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[190,1395,183,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[190,1396,183,1925]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Opisthoncus bellus (Karsch, 1878), male syntype. A: general appearance, dorsal view (with shape of cephalothorax); B: cephalothorax, frontal view (with chelicera); C – D: abdomen, lateral and dorsal views; E – F: chelicerae, ventral and lateral views; G – J: palpal organ, ventral and retrolateral views. Scale bars A, C, D: 1 mm; H, J: 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246502/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
Fig. 
<number box="[789,805,1442,1466]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
), about 
<quantity box="[902,970,1441,1466]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
long. Cephalothorax broadest anteriorly (CW = 
<number box="[236,265,1477,1502]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" value="86.0">86</number>
% of CL), moderately high (
<collectingCountry box="[583,624,1478,1502]" name="Switzerland" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">CH</collectingCountry>
= 
<number box="[654,683,1477,1502]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" value="50.0">50</number>
% of CL), dark brown, covered with whitish and orange scales and distinct cheek-swellings below ALE (
<figureCitation box="[574,642,1513,1538]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[190,1395,183,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[190,1396,183,1925]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Opisthoncus bellus (Karsch, 1878), male syntype. A: general appearance, dorsal view (with shape of cephalothorax); B: cephalothorax, frontal view (with chelicera); C – D: abdomen, lateral and dorsal views; E – F: chelicerae, ventral and lateral views; G – J: palpal organ, ventral and retrolateral views. Scale bars A, C, D: 1 mm; H, J: 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246502/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
Fig. 
<number box="[627,642,1514,1538]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Surrounding of eyes almost black. Clypeus narrow, with numerous whitish setae, overhanging towards chelicerae (
<figureCitation box="[706,778,1549,1574]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[190,1395,183,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[190,1396,183,1925]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Opisthoncus bellus (Karsch, 1878), male syntype. A: general appearance, dorsal view (with shape of cephalothorax); B: cephalothorax, frontal view (with chelicera); C – D: abdomen, lateral and dorsal views; E – F: chelicerae, ventral and lateral views; G – J: palpal organ, ventral and retrolateral views. Scale bars A, C, D: 1 mm; H, J: 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246502/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
Fig. 
<number box="[763,778,1550,1574]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Chelicerae, endites and labium brown, their anterior margins yellow. Sternum round, pale brown, with scattered brown hairs. Abdomen ovoid, with dorsal scutum, covered with brown bristles and pallid scales, colour pattern of longitudinal pallid area (guanine deposits) on brown-orange background (
<figureCitation box="[467,540,1657,1682]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[190,1395,183,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[190,1396,183,1925]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Opisthoncus bellus (Karsch, 1878), male syntype. A: general appearance, dorsal view (with shape of cephalothorax); B: cephalothorax, frontal view (with chelicera); C – D: abdomen, lateral and dorsal views; E – F: chelicerae, ventral and lateral views; G – J: palpal organ, ventral and retrolateral views. Scale bars A, C, D: 1 mm; H, J: 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246502/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
Figs 
<number box="[526,540,1658,1682]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
C–D). Venter greyish, spinnerets of similar colour. Legs orange-brown. Palpal organ (
<figureCitation box="[231,303,1693,1718]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[190,1395,183,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[190,1396,183,1925]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Opisthoncus bellus (Karsch, 1878), male syntype. A: general appearance, dorsal view (with shape of cephalothorax); B: cephalothorax, frontal view (with chelicera); C – D: abdomen, lateral and dorsal views; E – F: chelicerae, ventral and lateral views; G – J: palpal organ, ventral and retrolateral views. Scale bars A, C, D: 1 mm; H, J: 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246502/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
Figs 
<number box="[290,303,1694,1718]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
G–J) yellow-brown, tegulum elliptic, embolus moderately long, set at about 
<number box="[1180,1232,1694,1718]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" value="7.3">7.30</number>
, spermophore not meandering (in the type-specimen the bulbus is abnormally twisted; in figures 
<date box="[1089,1111,1730,1753]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
<number box="[1089,1102,1730,1753]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" value="7.0">7</number>
I
</date>
–J its position has been reconstructed).
</paragraph>
